sales=df.groupby('month year')['Sales'].sum().reset_index()
In [27]:
plt.figure(figsize=(15,6))
plt.plot(sales['month year'],sales['Sales'],linewidth=4)
plt.xticks(rotation='vertical')
plt.ylabel('Sales in USD')
plt.xlabel('yearly wise sales')
plt.title('Overall Sales Trend',size=25)
plt.show()

Observation :- As we can see in this graph that sales are increasing and company overall is growing.
